    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>White Bruges bobbin lace originating in the 19th century, made with a mix of whole stitch and half stitch with no raised work, and that exhibits bold floral forms. The groundwork consists of plaits, picots and decorated mesh grounds.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
